// Semantic direction:
// minnemodell defines the rules governing visibility of memory writes across CPU cores.
// modell_sekvensielt_konsistent gives the strongest guarantee: all operations appear globally ordered.
// modell_anskaffelse_frigjøring is the practical sweet spot: cheaper than SC, still prevents races.
// atomisk_sammenlign_og_bytt (CAS) is the primitive for all lock-free algorithms: set if unchanged.
// cas_svak may spuriously fail even when expected == actual, but is faster on some architectures.
// ordning_anskaffelse prevents later reads/writes from moving before this load.
// ordning_frigjøring prevents earlier reads/writes from moving after this store.
// synkroniseres_med is established by a release store observed by an acquire load.
// rase_betingelse occurs when two threads access the same memory without synchronization.
// hazard_pekere protect pointers from reclamation by registering them in hazard_register.
// hazard_scan checks all hazard registers before freeing retired nodes.
// epoke_basert_minne defers memory reclamation until all readers have left the current ebr_epoke.
// seqlock allows wait-free reads of a value guarded by a writer; readers retry on odd seqlock_versjon.
// falsk_deling occurs when independent variables share a cache_linje; cache_linje_polstring prevents it.
// tlsf (Two-Level Segregated Fit) allocator provides O(1) malloc and free with low fragmentation.
// arena_allokator bumps a pointer; arena_tilbakestill frees all allocations at once (O(1)).

// Primitive flow:
// atomisk CAS løkke: la forventet = atomisk_last(ptr, ordning_avslappet)
//   loop: ny = beregn(forventet)
//     cas_suksess = atomisk_sammenlign_og_bytt(ptr, forventet, ny, ansk_frigjøring, anskaffelse)
//     hvis cas_suksess: bryt | ellers: forventet = cas_resultat -> gjenta
// michael_scott_kø enqueue: new_node = allokér node
//   tail = atomisk_last(hale, anskaffelse)
//   loop: neste = atomisk_last(tail.neste, anskaffelse)
//     hvis neste == null: cas(tail.neste, null, new_node) -> suksess: cas(hale, tail, new_node)
//     ellers: cas(hale, tail, neste) [fremskritt hjelperen]
// seqlock les: loop: v1 = seqlock_versjon.last(anskaffelse) -> hvis odde: spin
//   les data -> v2 = seqlock_versjon.last(anskaffelse) -> hvis v1 != v2: gjenta

// This defines the memory model: SC/acquire-release/relaxed orderings, CAS, hazard pointers,
// epoch-based reclamation, seqlocks, lock-free queue/stack, and cache-line-aware allocation.
